## SEARCH BUTTON:

-Search box and a button.
-Now, I have to create a state useState() hook.
-When the user types something, I need to remember that value, and maybe do something with it (like filter data) when they click Search , that is why create a hook.
-Whenever state variables get updated , react triggers a reconcilliation cycle(re-renders the component)
-so we create a useState hook for searcTect.
-Then we create an other hook for , restaurants list as we are using the listOfRestaurants , when we press the search button , the list sorts out with the required restaurant list , now when we have to search for an other item , we will be searching from the previously modified list , so to avoid that it's better to search from the whole list , which can be stored in the new variable.

## useEffect(): (call back functions , dependencies)

-It tells React when to re-run the effect.(Usage of dependencies)
-if there is no dependency component , it gets called on every render.
-if dependency array is empty=[] useEffect is called on intital render(just once).
-If we put something is given in dependency, every time that changes , useeEffect is called.
-useEffect(callback, [dependencies])

## HOOKS:

-never use in conditional statements.
-anad write it in the functional component like body , header , dont put it inside.
-Keep it on the top.
-useState = stores and updates data inside your component.
-useEffect = reacts to changes (like “when the data changes, run this code”).
-const [state, setState] = useState(initialValue);

## ROUTER:

-If you build an app with multiple “pages” (Home, About, Cart, etc.), React doesn’t know how to move between them.
-It lets you build Single Page Applications (SPAs) where the URL changes (/home, /about, /cart), but the page doesn’t reload — React just swaps components.

-React Router is much more than just creating multiple images or basic links—it is a powerful library for managing client-side routing in React applications, enabling single-page applications (SPAs) to behave like multi-page apps without full page reloads.

- Whenever u want to create a router , first thing is to build react configuration.
  -Configuration means what will happen if something is called , what will happen at the route.
  -First import createBrowserRouter from react-router-dom.
  -Basically createBrowserRouter is used to create router ocnfiguration which includes path and the element to display when that path is chosen.(used to create paths)
  -Now , to reflect it on our app , we need to render it using RouterProvider.
  -First when we had to render , AppLayout component , we did it directly using root.render().

